{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3161541,"name":"khope","username":"khope","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/f6c823/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-03-10T04:26:07.850Z","cooked":"<p>This could possibly be the stupidest question of the night, but should our resetOdometry(Pose2d pose) method in our drive train subsystem be setting the gyro’s current angle to the angle in the pose that’s passed in?  Currently, ours is not and the robot is not behaving well when running a path planner auton when starting pointing at our driver’s station instead of away from it.  I thought we had path planner all worked out but it turns out the programmers were always teleoping the bot and zeroing out the gyro before practicing an auton so it always worked.</p>
<p>I’m guessing that it should be calling <code> gyro.setYaw(pose.getRototation().getDegrees());</code>   I don’t recall where we got our sample resetOdometry code from to begin with.</p>
<pre><code>public void resetOdometry(Pose2d pose) {
    odometry.resetPosition(pose.getRotation(),
            getPositions(),
            pose);
}
</code></pre>
<p>Or should we be doing this somewhere else in the code?  I feel like the the Gyro needs to know what angle it’s positioned at when we start.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2023-03-10T04:39:34.704Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":76,"reads":79,"readers_count":78,"score":410.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":429684,"topic_slug":"should-resetodometry-set-gyro-angle","display_username":"khope","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":31620,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4779 - The RoboSapiens"},"post_url":"/t/should-resetodometry-set-gyro-angle/429684/1","custom_user_title":"4779 - The RoboSapiens","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true,"can_vote":false},{"id":3161564,"name":"Nolan","username":"Quake","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/quake/{size}/236072_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-10T04:41:35.133Z","cooked":"<p>When you reset the odometry, you should pass in the current gyro angle (instead of the pose rotation) to that first parameter. The gyro angle is used to determine an offset-- that is, if your gyro yaw reads 20 degrees and you reset to a pose with a yaw rotation of 0, the odometry pose rotation would be <code>(gyro yaw - 20 degrees)</code>. The pose you pass in the final parameter includes the translation and rotation you are resetting to.</p>
<p>This also means that your gyro angles may not match your odometry, and you should use the odometry pose for any field-centric tasks.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2023-03-10T04:41:35.133Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":75,"readers_count":74,"score":40.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":429684,"topic_slug":"should-resetodometry-set-gyro-angle","display_username":"Nolan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":37917,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4512AM"},"post_url":"/t/should-resetodometry-set-gyro-angle/429684/2","custom_user_title":"4512AM","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3161565,"name":"khope","username":"khope","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/f6c823/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-03-10T04:51:06.017Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks for the help, does this look better?  My gyroscope is Pigeon2.</p>
